Articles.Content: I'm trying to build a shuttle bay tilting platform to launch a satellite but the hinges won't move with a decoupler attached. As soon as I stage the decoupler, the hinge will move. The decouplers in question are BDB decouplers. Is this a limitation in the hinges or am I doing something wrong?

Further info, it's not the decoupler itself. Removing the entire probe and the the decoupler rotates. Putting the base of the probe, minus the probe core  and the decoupler and it rotates. Add the decoupler back and it fails. I'm trying variations of probe core and parts stacks and what I can find is that you can't rotate a probe core nor an RCS system. Normal behavior?

Do you have any autostruts on the probe and/or the decoupler? These will keep anything in place. KJR can cause this issue as well (funny thing though: The release version of "KJR Next" sometimes causes troubles while the debug version works fine)

1 hour ago, 4x4cheesecake said:

Do you have any autostruts on the probe and/or the decoupler? These will keep anything in place. KJR can cause this issue as well (funny thing though: The release version of "KJR Next" sometimes causes troubles while the debug version works fine)

Nothing is autostruted. I do have KJR next installed. Would KJR continued be a better choice?

Just now, birdog357 said:

Nothing is autostruted. I do have KJR next installed. Would KJR continued be a better choice?

 

As far as I know, "KJR Next" is the only version which supports the robotic parts. Like I said, the debug version works fine, so you may want to try it:

https://github.com/meirumeiru/Kerbal-Joint-Reinforcement/releases/tag/v4.0.13

(Download and install the "KerbalJointReinforcement_dbg_v4.0.13.zip", obviously, you have to uninstall the regular version The debug version just adds a simple UI to display and enable/disable some struts)
Apparently, there is also a pre-release for the next version which is supposed to fix this issue but I don't know any details, just found it in the repository^^
Awesome. I'll have to install that on my next load up. Twelve minutes is too long of a load time to do a hot swap...

2 hours ago, birdog357 said:

Nothing is autostruted. I do have KJR next installed. Would KJR continued be a better choice?

 

Is there landing gear on the thing? If the hinge is heavy enough then the gear could be strutted to it. (landing gear/wheels force autostrutting to heaviest part)

23 hours ago, Starwaster said:

Is there landing gear on the thing? If the hinge is heavy enough then the gear could be strutted to it. (landing gear/wheels force autostrutting to heaviest part)

Yes there is. It's a shuttle style craft.

20 minutes ago, birdog357 said:

Yes there is. It's a shuttle style craft.

Use the 'visualize autostruts' in the cheat menu (F-12) and see where they are being strutted to.

It's hard to imagine that the hinges are the heaviest thing on there but if that's where the gear is strutting to then that could be why they aren't moving.

Maybe also upload a copy of the craft file so we can take a look at it? Maybe try to figure out a solution?

1 hour ago, Starwaster said:

t's hard to imagine that the hinges are the heaviest thing on there

Doesn't matter. Autostruts very often attach to the first robotic part they find as they make their way up the .craft tree towards what you actually wanted to strut them to.
